## Part 5: COMPUTE STRATEGY

| Task | Where | Cost | Why There |
|---|---|---|---|
| Code writing | Your laptop | Free | Just code, no GPU needed |
| YOLO fine-tuning | Google Colab (T4) | Free | 15GB VRAM fits YOLOv11s, 12hr sessions |
| Long training runs | Vast.ai (A10) | ~$0.20/hr | For runs that exceed Colab timeouts |
| Data collection | Cheap CPU VM | ~$5/mo | Scraping images doesn't need GPU |
| Tracking inference | Colab T4 | Free | BoxMOT runs on T4 |
| Prediction training | Colab T4 | Free | 87-node graph is tiny |
| Dashboard hosting | Railway (free) | Free | Static dashboard, no GPU |

**Total estimated cost: $10-20 for the entire project**

> [!CAUTION]
> **Azure for Students ($100) does NOT give GPU access.** The GPU quota is zero by default and can't be increased on student accounts. Don't plan around it.

