## Part 6: BUILD ORDER — What Comes First and Why

```
Phase 1: Data Collection (2 weeks, no GPU needed)
   Why first: Everything depends on having data. Start collecting
   while you work on models.
     │
Phase 2: Detection (fine-tuning YOLO)
   Why second: Detection is the foundation. You can't track, count,
   or predict without first detecting vehicles.
     │
Phase 3: Tracking (BoT-SORT setup)
   Why third: Tracking converts detections into trajectories,
   counts, and speeds — the raw material for analytics.
     │
Phase 4: Understanding (counting, speed, congestion scoring)
   Why fourth: Turn raw tracking data into metrics. This is where
   you build the feature vectors for prediction.
     │
Phase 5: Prediction (LSTM baseline → Graph upgrade)
   Why fifth: You need historical metrics from Phase 4 before you
   can predict. Start simple, add complexity.
     │
Phase 6: Anomaly + Failure + Drift
   Why sixth: You need a running system to monitor. These layers
   analyze the system itself.
     │
Phase 7: Dataset packaging + Dashboard + Benchmarks
   Why last: Polish and publish. Format everything for Kaggle,
   build the visual dashboard, write benchmark reports.
```

**Key insight:** Phases 1 and 2 can run in parallel — collect data on a CPU VM while fine-tuning YOLO on Colab.

